## Performance Impact

### Health Check Endpoint
- **Response Time**: ~50-150ms
- **Database Query**: 1 simple SELECT
- **Cache Check**: 1 write + 1 read + 1 delete
- **Overhead**: Minimal (runs only when called)

### Error Logging
- **Write Time**: <1ms per log entry
- **Log Rotation**: Automatic when file > 10MB
- **Disk Usage**: 10-50MB per week (estimated)

---

## Monitoring Best Practices

### 1. Regular Health Checks
- Check `/health` endpoint every 5-15 minutes
- Alert on status changes from `healthy` to `degraded`
- Monitor disk space warnings

### 2. Log Management
- Review error logs daily/weekly
- Archive old logs monthly
- Set up alerts for CRITICAL errors

### 3. Cache Monitoring
- Check cache hit rates via `/health/stats`
- Monitor cache directory size
- Clean expired cache regularly (handled automatically)

### 4. Performance Tracking
- Monitor API response times
- Track database query durations
- Identify slow endpoints for optimization

